Task: 06
Title: Domain types and services for ensemble
Phase: 2
Route: full
Slice: Panel Fan-out + Synthesis, Judge Analysis
Dependencies: 05
Scope: Add domain types and pure services needed for the ensemble pipeline: PanelResponse and PanelResult discriminated union (fulfilled/rejected per model), synthesis prompt builder (concatenates panel outputs), Analysis zod schema (consensus, contradictions, uniqueInsights, blindSpots with safeParse export), and judge prompt builder (constructs system/user prompts requesting structured analysis). All additions are pure domain code with no application or infrastructure imports.
Acceptance Criteria: AC-7 (partial — panel types, prompt), AC-8 (partial — analysis schema, judge prompt), AC-9 (partial — synthesis prompt builder)
NFRs: NFR-1, NFR-5 (types support graceful degradation)
Gate Criteria: Phase 2 Gate 1 (domain types ready for ensemble), Phase 2 Gate 2 (schema supports safeParse degradation)
Files:
  - src/domain/model/panel-types.ts (CREATE) — PanelResponse (model ref, content, usage, latency) and PanelResult discriminated union (fulfilled | rejected per model)
  - src/domain/services/prompt-builders.ts (CREATE) — buildSynthesisPrompt(panelResponses: PanelResponse[], analysis?: Analysis): string — concatenates panel outputs and optional analysis fields into a synthesis prompt
  - src/domain/services/analysis-schema.ts (CREATE) — Zod schema for Analysis (consensus, contradictions, uniqueInsights, blindSpots); safeParseAnalysis() export returning discriminated union; inferred Analysis, Contradiction, UniqueInsight types
  - src/domain/services/judge-prompt-builder.ts (CREATE) — buildJudgePrompt(panelResponses: PanelResponse[]): { systemPrompt: string; userPrompt: string } — constructs structured-analysis prompt
